summary=["New Zealand Endeavour trumped the locals in 1992, Sayonara won in 1995 and German's Morning Glory set a race record of two days, 14 hours, seven minutes and 10 seconds the following year.Race spokesman Peter Campbell said it was not known how long the sailor washed overboard could survive in the water.The yacht, which has a crew of 11, was halfway across Bass Strait when it overturned.The two dead were found on the 40-foot vessel Business Post Naiad, about 100 kilometers 60 miles off the New South Wales state town of Merimbula, according to the Australian Search and Rescue Coordination Center AusSAR in Canberra. United States maxi Sayonara looks set to continue the foreign domination of line honors in Australia's famous Sydney to Hobart yacht race, which starts Saturday"]